box-sizing: border-box; -> If we add padding or border on element, it does not effect the width of it
display:flex -> Center everything
height: 100vh; -> take entire height of browser
background-color:lighten(orange, 45%);

Specificity: Which styles to listen to when two or more styles are competing.
Class selectors are specific than descendent selectors.
Descendent selector with class is specific than class selector. footer .hello{}



Note:
-----
- flex-direction and align-items are related. Alignment will happen accordign to direction. If column then horizontal.





.container{
    max-width:940px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding-left:40px;
    padding-right:40px;
}


Attaching css:
---------------
<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/style.css">

Styles:
-------
color:orange
text-align:center;

Selectors:
----------
1) Type selectors:

2) Descendent selectors:
header p span{

}

3) Class selectors:
.xyz {
    color:yellow
}

Box model:
----------
width->padding-> border -> margin
box-sizing:border-box; // Width 250px would mean -> width+padding+border

Layout and floats:
------------------
<div class="container group"></div>
.container{
    max-width:940px;
    margin-left:auto;
    margin-right:auto;
}

.main-area{
    width:66%;
    float:left;
}

.sidebar{
    width:34%;
    float:left;
}

.group:before,
.group:after{
  content:"";
  display:table;
}

.group:after{
    clear:both;
}

.group{
    zoom:1;
}

Create a div below sidebar and then put it above style:

Styling navigation:
-------------------
<nav class="site-nav">

 <ul class="group">
   <li><a></a></li>
   <li></li>
 </ul> 

</nav>


.site-nav li{
  float:left;
  list-style:none;
}

.site-nav ul{
  margin:0;
  padding:0;
}

.site-nav a{
    display:block;
}


Color:
-------
rgba(0,0,0,opacity)

Remember:
----------
display:block;
z-index:10;


Measurements:
--------------
em -> base size is defined interms of parents elements 
rem -> it is em except the base size is always the root font size.

